The paper deals with modulation schemes and multiple access techniques in wireless communication systems, which are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), communication systems (cs.COMM), signal processing (cs.SY), networking (cs.NI), and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of delay-Doppler domain and OTFS modulation also suggests a focus on signal processing and communication systems. Therefore, these five categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
